Description: WEN Hair Care offers shampoos in a competitive market, having sold over 40 million bottles.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: WEN Hair Care was founded on the belief that beautiful hair can and should be achieved without sacrificing your hair's health.No harsh sulfates that lather—just fuller, stronger, healthier-looking hair. WEN® brings a completely different approach to the way you cleanse your hair. Chaz Dean, world-renowned hair expert and Creator of WEN, got his start in developing hair care products at a popular Beverly Hills salon, where he worked as an assistant to the manager. With no prior experience in product development, Chaz was asked to help create a deep conditioner for the salon's own product line.  While some would think he was in over his head, Chaz embraced the challenge and about nine months later, launched a product for his first time. He gained the trust and confidence of the company, and just three months later, he was asked to develop a natural product line. All this ... at the age of just 21.  After more than a year of careful testing using both sides of Chaz's own head, the product line was finally launched. It featured a primrose shampoo, rosemary conditioner and sage conditioner. Word spread fast about the concept of cleansing hair without lather, creating a snowball effect among Hollywood celebrities. Since many of them were actors who had to style their hair for shows, they would come into his salon with damaged hair—all eager to learn how to get shinier, more manageable, healthier-looking hair. It's because of Chaz's relentless drive that WEN® has become a worldwide success. Since WEN® was created 16 years ago, it has sold 40 million bottles and is loved by hundreds of thousands of customers worldwide, from Asia, to Latin America, to the Middle East.

Full Description: Founded in 1977, Epic has a rich heritage of technological advancements in the printing industry. Epic began by developing and commercializing the first dampening system that virtually eliminates printing defects or “hickeys”. In doing so, the quality and efficiency of offset printing presses was greatly improved. The Epic Delta Dampening System was so advanced that, still today every major press manufacturer incorporates a dampening system based on Epic’s technology. Epic is also credited for significant innovations in offset and digital coating technologies. Epic was the first company to retrofit an offset printing press with a coater. Additionally, when Xerox Corporation was looking for a company to develop a coater to run in-line with their iGen presses, they turned to Epic to develop a solution. Epic is now a recognized Xerox Innovation Partner. Epic’s founder and CEO, Harvey Dahlgren is an industry icon. Since Epic’s inception, Harvey has worked closely with Epic employees to develop and commercialize products. This tradition in research, engineering and manufacturing established by Mr. Dahlgren, motivates Epic today to look for new solutions to improve the printing process.

Description: Based in Glen Burnie, Summit Consulting provides sales consulting to large corporations in the energy sector | Twitter @ SummitConsultng
Headquarters Regions: Greater Baltimore-Maryland Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: It’s a Friday morning in Glen Burnie, MD at Summit Consulting and the energy is high! Not only because it’s Friday, that’s just the type of team they are – high energy, excited about their work, and enjoy getting pumped up for the day! The music is up, employees are joking around with each other and everyone is getting ready for one of their favorite days of the week. You see, it’s an office tradition that on every Friday employees have the opportunity to “throw down” with one another. Of course not in a physical sense (that would not be condoned). A “throw down” is simply a challenge, a competition, where two or more people set forth a bet as to who will outperform the other for that day. It’s all in good fun of course but the Summit Consulting employees thrive on fun challenges like this! Part of the Glen Burnie team’s competitive nature comes from the fact that many of them are former athletes. Some even played at a collegiate level in sports such as track and field, soccer, baseball, basketball, wrestling, and hockey! Many others are simply sports fans. Lots of Philadelphia Eagles supporters, but some other teams that are represented at Summit Consulting include, Baltimore Ravens, Baltimore Orioles, Penn State football, Philadelphia Flyers and the Washington Capitals. It’s a diverse group but they all share one thing – the love to compete! And Management doesn’t mind one bit! As long as they are conducting themselves in a professional manner and operating with integrity they are totally on board, even join in from time to time! After all, competition typically improves performances. So what is the outcome from these “throw downs”? Well, it really is whatever is agreed upon between both parties. Usually, it ends up being something like the loser has to bring coffee in for the winner the following morning, or, everyone’s favorite, “biggest fan”. What that means is the loser essentially has to be the winner’s “hype man” for a day. If you’ve never had your own hype man, you’re definitely missing out! And let’s not forget the best part about winning your “throw down”… bragging rights.  To find out more about the unique company culture of Summit Consulting, be sure to follow them on LinkedIn.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Energy, Professional Services, Sales and Marketing, Sustainability

Description: Kadaxis develops marketing software for self-published authors.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Kadaxis helps publishers to dramatically increase the long term ROI on a title, by analyzing the full text of books to derive metadata and increase discoverability. More books are sold through e-retailers than in stores, and one of the core contributors to successful discoverability, is an online book presence with metadata and copy optimized for search engines. An increase in volume of high quality search traffic directly correlates to an increase in online conversions. Kadaxis enables publishers, both indie and traditional, to extract keywords, phrases and other metadata from the text of a book, then selects and ranks this data based on current trends and relevance. This helps publishers leverage the wealth of content within each book, by exposing the topics most likely to lead to a conversion. As different trends emerge, new keywords highlighting different elements of a book will attract the most traffic. By treating a book's description and metadata as dynamic, publishers can increase the return on their initial investment in a title, by attracting a larger audience over time.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Blackwave provides an integrated infrastructure platform for the storage and delivery of video over IP. Blackwaveâ€™s core value proposition is to significantly lower the cost and increase the simplicity of building, scaling and managing the infrastructure required to stream deep libraries of video content to a large, concurrent audience. Blackwave infrastructure significantly reduces both the required Cap-Ex and the ongoing Op-Ex associated with IP video delivery through breakthroughs in the way video data is stored and read from standard disk drives. A system begins with 48TBs of storage coupled with 10Gbps delivery capacity. Both storage and delivery are independently scalable, and the system natively manages video delivery via HTTP, Flash, and WMS protocols through a single web UI. Today, Telcos, CDNs, content aggregators and distributors deploy the Blackwave system for use anywhere from the storage-intensive Origin to distributed nodes at the Edge of their content delivery network.  The company brought their first system to market in the US and Asia in February, 2009, and announced their first customer, CDNetworks, shortly thereafter.

Description: The SEAL Future Fund’s (SFF) mission is to provide resources to equip active duty and veteran Navy SEALs for success in the civilian world.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The SEAL Future Foundation’s (SFF) mission is to provide resources to equip active duty and veteran Navy SEALs for success in the civilian world. Navy SEALs are among the most highly trained  professionals in the world, serving as paragons of leadership, teamwork, resolution, and focus. As individuals who excel under extreme conditions, executing tasks with outcomes that are measured in life and freedom, their qualities are invaluable to any organization. The SFF is focused on ensuring that these individuals and their capabilities are not lost in the posterity of duty. From educational scholarships to job placement and networking opportunities, the SFF provides SEALs with countless pathways to success within the communities they fought so hard to protect. The SFF was created in response to the lack of support for continuing education and career development for active and veteran Navy SEALs. High tuitions, limited financial resources and lack of access to professional networks combine to prevent these exceptional individuals from reaching their full potential in civilian life.  The SFF focuses its resources on career development and educational opportunities by partnering with academic institutions, corporations and individuals.  Under this model we are able to support each accepted applicant regardless of his stage of post-military life, whether it is by providing a college scholarship, funding an internship, matching with a professional mentor or providing permanent job placement services. By helping to surmount these initial barriers, we can empower SEALs to excel in the civilian world just as they did in their military careers. Tax ID# 46-0565393

As a result, iasset.com was born. Building on the success of Distribution Central, which within 6 months, took its renewal rate from 40% to 90%, the founders realised the potential the platform could have across other companies and incorporated it as a separate business entity. Today iasset.com has a global customer base and manages over $7.5B in assets across various companies in the IT channel. The strength of the platform lies in it’s automation of a renewals process and its ability to build accurate installed base information.

Description: SOLVY is your personal guide to real-life math. It helps users discover the power of math as a tool for solving real-world problems.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: SOLVY addresses the epidemic of innumeracy through a proprietary interactive online platform that allows students to learn, explore and enjoy mathematics in their own personalized way, and gives teachers the tools to reduce routine work and concentrate on actual teaching. Problem The way mathematics is taught is test-oriented and lecture-based. ‘Modern’ educational systems prepare students for the exams, but not for solving real-life problems. They also deprive students of an ability to try their own ways to solve problems before hearing a lecture about them. As a result, many students don’t see how mathematics can help them in the real world, so how can they be interested and passionate about it? Breakthrough Unlike existing systems, SOLVY is not another online textbook. While aligned with the official Common Core curriculum, it allows for multiple ways to solve a problem, and the students can get step-by-step feedback on their solutions – much like from a human teacher. Their teachers, in turn, will get automatic reports on student performance and knowledge gaps without spending nights on tedious grading of homework. Why Does It Matter? Literacy and numeracy are recognized as cornerstones for the future success of our children, and yet many countries, rich and poor, struggle to achieve them. Lack of resources, or recalcitrant legacy teaching systems lead different countries, from the USA and UK to Brazil to failure or mediocrity in mathematics. Without a solution to the innumeracy problem, our kids will not only fail at the university, but will also have real troubles in their financial and professional lives.
